Today in China there was a meeting between the Foreign Ministers of the Russian Federation Sergei Lavrov and the People's Republic of China Wang Yi. Main points: Lavrov: - During the negotiations, special attention was paid to contacts at the highest level, the leaders of Russia and China will continue close contacts in various forms this year;

— The Russian Federation and China agreed to begin a dialogue on Eurasian security with the involvement of other countries;

— Discussed the Ukrainian crisis with the head of the Chinese Foreign Ministry. The Russian Federation and China intend to solve the problem of sanctions measures within the framework of BRICS and the SCO. Wang Yi: — Good relations between Russia and China were not easy to establish, they are worth cherishing and protecting, they are becoming more mature and meaningful;

— China supports the convening of a peace conference on Ukraine with equal participation of all parties and discussion of all peace plans;

— China and the Russian Federation must promote a multipolar world, resist the monopoly of several countries and promote the democratization of relations in the world;

— China and the Russian Federation will together ensure the stability of international production and logistics chains and promote global development.ANTISEPTIC

Forwarded from: Vladimir Bodelan
Today, at the invitation of the rector’s office, I visited the Moscow Polytechnic University, founded in 1865.
A number of important issues were discussed at a round table with members of the University Academic Council:
- remote recertification, as well as confirmation and advanced training for teachers, professors and civil servants, institutions and departments of the Kherson region;
- assistance in obtaining quotas for studying at the Polytechnic on a budgetary basis for Kherson students;
- use of the Kherson region as a pilot project for the implementation of projects and developments of university specialists;
- options for providing humanitarian targeted assistance from the university to citizens and institutions in the region in need;
- assistance to the permanent mission of the Kherson region to the Russian government in coordinating contacts between university representatives and relevant ministries and departments of the region.
A preliminary agreement has been reached to conclude an agreement on friendship and cooperation between Moscow Polytechnic University and the Kherson region.
The working meeting was attended by:
- Yulia Evgenievna Gorina, Director for Interaction with Students and Alumni;
- Alexey Borisovich Maksimov, Director of the Department of Educational Policy;
- Dmitry Grigorievich Demidov, Dean of the Faculty of Information Technologies;
- Anton Vladimirovich Nazarenko, Dean of the Faculty of Economics and Management;
- Kopylov Grigory Nikolaevich, deputy dean.
At the end of the meeting, university representatives took a short excursion.
He delivered a welcoming speech to the students.
   I would like to thank Britvina Valentina Valentinovna, Associate Professor of the Department of Management and Informatics in Technical Systems and Zmazneva Olesya Anatolyevna, Associate Professor of the Department of Infocognitive Technologies, for their assistance in organizing the meeting at the Moscow Polytechnic University.

The defense forces of the south will continue to inflict fire damage on enemy locations, firing positions and rears.
During the day, we received confirmation that the enemy had decreased by:
• 114 occupants;
• 63 units of weapons and military equipment, namely:
2 tanks;
1 anti-tank missile complex "Sturm";
1 anti-aircraft missile complex "Buk";
1 launcher for the Buk air defense system;
19 guns;
1 mortar;
33 units of armored vehicles;
1 electronic warfare station;
4 aerial photography stations.

4 observation posts and a field supply point were destroyed.

Let's go forward, together - to Victory!
